Level "Placeholder" is an anomalous level of the Backrooms.

== Description ==

=== Layer 1 ===
The first layer of the Level "Placeholder," which from now on will be referred to as a "Manifestation," is the area and/or phenomenon in which a section of an already existing or newly emerging level is generating a new section of itself. These sections vary in size, as they can reach sizes as small as 500 square meters (1640.42 square feet) up to 180 square kilometers (111.847 square miles). A manifestation is temporary, and all manifestations of layer 1 will generate a level.

There was a point in the Backrooms when Level Placeholder did not exist. Over 600 million square miles of randomly segmented rooms were generated millions of years ago when Level 0 was the only one to ever exist. Over time, new levels got generated with pre-generated areas. Eventually, all entities and humans would explore every square mile, with entities contributing over 99.99% of that exploration. Due to this, a backrooms-wide earthquake occurred that lasted over 7 hours on January 6th, 1698. During these 7 hours, it is presumed that Level Placeholder, along with Cluster II was being created. After this, a sudden influx of new levels began appearing. However, the first records of layer 2 of Level Placeholder were only found on May 3rd, 1851. Suddenly, on March 5th, 2023, all communication between Cluster II+ and Cluster I would be cut off. Since then, Cluster II has never been contacted, and therefore all its levels are no longer in [[M.E.G.|the M.E.G.'s]] archives. As of now, there are roughly 1180 numbered levels in the Backrooms, most of these being undocumented. Cluster II will likely not reappear until a massive number of these levels have been explored majorly.

There is a very common part of lots of levels in the Backrooms - Instances. It is known that many levels have instances. Every single instance is unique per person. Trying to generate an instance as a wanderer is entering that instance; it will be almost impossible for the Backrooms to accomplish that. Therefore, it "made a system" that knows if a wanderer is close to a junction of entrances & exits that lead to an instance-based level.

<big>Example</big>

If the backrooms detected that a wanderer was roughly a varying amount of levels away from an instance-based level, it would begin generating that wanderer's specific instance. The varying amount depends on how fast it is possible to get to the instance-based level.


<big>Manifestations are the main part of layer 1. Layer 1 has no physical form - its manifestations do.</big>

=== Manifestations ===
Manifestations of the level "Placeholder" have different properties, and each manifestation has a difference from the other one. They are also easily predictable of what they will transform into when they are being created; if they are being created right next to an existing level, the manifestation of the level will become an expanded part of the level it was next to and be one with the newly expanded level. These manifestations have been researched by the [[M.E.G.]] and it appears that the Backrooms generates areas using level "Placeholder" over 10 kilometers (6.213 miles) away from a person's location.

<center><big>Stage 1: "Void"</big></center>
The first stage of a manifestation is a fully unloaded area that has not gotten a signal to start generating or has just only started to generate. It resembles a simple black void, like [[the Void]] of the Backrooms. This stage only lasts roughly 10 seconds after generation begins.

<center><big>Stage 2: "Structure"</big></center>
{{Blurimage|file=RIWE906.592TKHEOIT0.jpg|caption=A Manifestation of level 0 being created from level "Placeholder" during stage 2.}}
The second stage of a manifestation happens immediately the first stage ends. During this stage, the manifestation will begin to construct its walls, floor, and ceiling seemingly by extruding itself from any close-by matter. [[M.E.G.|The M.E.G.]] attempted to research where this matter comes from but has been unable to do so. these walls, floors, and roofs will have random colors assigned, which usually resemble the level it's transforming into. This stage lasts around 20 seconds. Up to stage 4, manifestations will appear as if they were created in a cheap rendering engine from around the 90s.

<big><center>Stage 3: "Detail"</center></big>
The third stage happens roughly 5 seconds after Stage 2 finishes. During stage 3, the manifestation will begin to have furniture and other details such as ceiling lights. The surfaces will also become uneven. If the parent level doesn't have any of these, then it'll simply wait roughly for 10 seconds.

<big><center>Stage 4: "Texture"</center></big>
The fourth stage happens almost immediately after stage 3 finishes. During this stage, the manifestation will have all its surfaces start to mush as if in "colors mixing in very weird patterns." These mushy texture transformations will morph into the level's corresponding textures of the wall. This stage lasts roughly 40 seconds. If one stands within a manifestation during Stage 4, they could be dragged and mixed with the texture transformation, becoming one with the level.

<center><big>Stage 5: "Cleaning"</big></center>
The final stage happens a few seconds after stage 4 starts, working at the same time. Stage 5 simply flattens out the surfaces into what is needed. This lasts just around 5 seconds after stage 4 ends. The end of this stage is when a manifestation of "Placeholder" has fully transformed into part of a level.

=== Layer 2 ===
Layer 2 is a severely unstable area to be in, as this layer contains UPA - info on UPA is available in the entities section. Most of layer 2's information comes from archives dated before January 2nd 2025 - this is due to 9 M.E.G. researchers disappearing in just 22 days in December of 2024 after entering layer 2. Layer 2 resembles pure white and featureless hallways. The floors, walls, and ceiling of Layer 2 are all made out of an unknown glossy and very flat material. Touching these materials is safe. The hallways of layer 2 are non-euclidean. Very rarely, stairs made out of the same material can be found. They typically lead upstairs, and once one goes upstairs, the stairs will seemingly disappear. Another feature of the hallways are Windows (Not to be confused with the entity.) that do not emit visible light, but attempting to view the outside through these windows will only show a bright white glow that is impossible to see through, these windows are indestructible as well. There is an unknown light source on layer 2 that does not come from the windows. Attempting to block this unknown light source always results in failure.

== Colonies & Outposts ==
Due to the extreme impact layer 2 has on someone's mind and layer 1 being temporary, it is not advised at all to try to create and/or maintain any colonies/outposts here - the M.E.G.

== Entities ==
=== Unknown Powerful Anomaly ===
"Unknown Powerful Anomaly," commonly abbreviated as UPA, is a highly undocumented entity that lives on layer 2. Wanderers who survived layer 2 described "It laughed at me... It tortured me, I could only see the exit through an invisible wall, then as it got rid of the invisible wall - it got rid of the exit too. It fed off my pain.". It is presumed that this entity is very powerful and can torture wanderers at will. This entity was discovered on February 15th, 2025, and performing research on it is very dangerous. Therefore [[M.E.G.|The M.E.G.]] has refused at least 6 different proposals to test on UPA since March 2nd, 2025.
